definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lie, to not tell the truth; to lie to (someone)","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"كَذَبَنِي الْحَدِيثَ","english":"He lied to me in his speech."},{"text":"وَكَمِ ٱنْتَشْتَ بِٱلسُّيُوفِ مِنَ الدَّهْـ / ـرِ أَسِيرًا وَبِٱلنَّوَالِ مُقِلَّا\nعَدَّهَا نُصْرَةً عَلَيْهِ فَلَمَّا / صَالَ خَتْلًا رَآهُ أَدْرَكَ تَبْلَا\nكَذَبَتْهُ ظُنُونُهُ أَنْتَ تُبْلِيـ / ـهِ وَتَبْقَى فِي نِعْمَةٍ لَيْسَ تَبَلَّى"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to lie, to not tell the truth; to lie about (عَلَى (ʕalā))","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"فَمَنْ أَظْلَمُ مِمَّن كَذَبَ عَلَى ٱللَّهِ وَكَذَّبَ بِٱلصِّدْقِ إِذْ جَاءَهُ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deceive"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to allege of lying, to disbelieve someone","examples":[{"text":"وَأَخِي هَارُونُ هُوَ أَفْصَحُ مِنِّي لِسَانًا فَأَرْسِلْهُ مَعِيَ رِدْءًا يُصَدِّقُنِيۖ إِنِّي أَخَافُ أَن يُكَذِّبُونِ","english":"My brother Aaron is more eloquent than me in speech. Therefor send him with me as a helper to confirm me. Lo! I fear that they will give the lie to me."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to accuse or tell that something is false or deceitful, to disbelieve","examples":[{"text":"كَذَّبَ الْخَبَرَ","english":"He didn't believe the news."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to disbelieve in","examples":[{"text":"وَكَذَّبُوا بِآيَاتِنَا كِذَّابًا","english":"They called Our revelations false with strong denial."},{"text":"إِنَّ سَعْيَكُمْ لَشَتَّى\n فَأَمَّا مَنْ أَعْطَى وَٱتَّقَى\n وَصَدَّقَ بِٱلْحُسْنَى\n فَسَنُيَسِّرُهُ لِلْيُسْرَى\n وَأَمَّا مَن بَخِلَ وَٱسْتَغْنَى\n وَكَذَّبَ بِٱلْحُسْنَى\n فَسَنُيَسِّرُهُ لِلْعُسْرَى","english":"Lo! your effort is dispersed (toward divers ends).\nAs for him who giveth and is dutiful (toward Allah)\nAnd believeth in goodness;\nSurely We will ease his way unto the state of ease.\nBut as for him who hoardeth and deemeth himself independent,\nAnd disbelieveth in goodness;\nSurely We will ease his way unto adversity."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make (someone) disbelieve (in)","tags":["rare"],"examples":[{"text":"فَمَا يُكَذِّبُكَ بَعْدُ بِالدِّينِ"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to disprove, to refute"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be inactive, to be deactivated"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to abstain, to desist"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of كَذَبَ (kaḏaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lying","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lie, falsehood, untruth","tags":["uncountable"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"false","examples":[{"text":"وَجَاءُوا عَلَىٰ قَمِيصِهِ بِدَمٍ كَذِبٍ","english":"And they brought his shirt and stained it with false blood."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew כָּזָב (kazáv, “to lie, to deceive, to mislead”) and Classical Syriac ܟܕܒܐ (kaddɑvɑ, “liar”)."},"ipa":["/ka.ða.ba/"]}